p
\sum_{k=2}^{\infty} \frac{k}{\left(k^3-k\right)^p}
\displaystyle a_k = \frac{k}{(k^3 - k)^p}
\displaystyle b_k = \frac{k}{(k^3)^p}
a_k/b_k \to 1
k \to +\infty
\frac k{(k^3-k)^p}=\frac1{k^{p-1}(k^2-1)^p}
p=1\implies\sum_{k=2}^\infty\frac1{k^2-k}=\sum_{k=2}^\infty\left(\frac1{k-1}-\frac1k\right)=1-\frac12+\frac12-\frac13+\ldots
p=\frac12\implies\sum_{k=2}^\infty\sqrt{\frac k{k^2-k}}=\sum_{k=2}^\infty\frac 1{\sqrt{k-1}}\;\ldots
